file=Cybersecurity/keyring/custom/identity-lifecycle/assets/jml-checklist.md · jc—:JML Checklist — keyring/identity-lifecycle=> keyring specs; operator/IdP executes (security-inversion). Every change logged. Leaver = ALL systems.\n · j:Joiner=- [ ] Role identified → least-privilege access set (not "what last person had")\n- [ ] Access granted by operator/IdP per the set; no over-provisioning\n- [ ] MFA enrolled; account logged\n · m(c:Mover (role change)=- [ ] New role's access added\n- [ ] **Old role's access REMOVED** (not additive)\n- [ ] Net access = current role only; logged\n · l(l:Leaver (the loudest gap)=- [ ] IdP/SSO account disabled promptly\n- [ ] SaaS NOT behind SSO — each revoked\n- [ ] Shared / service accounts they used — rotated\n- [ ] API keys / tokens / secrets they held — revoked (→ secrets-governance)\n- [ ] Physical/VPN/device access removed\n- [ ] Time-to-deprovision recorded (metric)\n · r(:Reconcile (cadence)=- [ ] Every account ↔ a current person with a current need\n- [ ] Orphans (no owner) / ghosts (departed) / shared logins flagged → warden register\n